#Task-6

1. Built a full-stack Movie Search Application using React.js for the frontend and FastAPI for the backend.

2. Implemented user authentication with Register and Login functionality using JWT token-based authentication.

3. Used FastAPI routes to handle APIs for user registration, login, movie search, and favorite movies management.

4. Integrated the OMDb API to fetch movie details dynamically based on the movie title entered by the user.

5. Stored user details and favorite movies data using SQLite database with SQLAlchemy ORM.

6. Used password hashing with bcrypt and Passlib to securely store user passwords in the database.

7. Implemented protected APIs using Bearer Token authentication for adding and viewing favorite movies.

8. Created responsive movie cards in React with movie poster, title, year, and type information.

9. Added “Add to Favorites” functionality with duplicate favorite checking to prevent repeated entries.

10. Improved frontend UI using separate CSS files, loading indicators, error handling, alerts, and responsive grid layouts for better user experience.


11. React Hooks like `useState` were used to manage form inputs, loading states, movie data, and error messages in the frontend.

12. React Router was used for navigation between Login, Register, and Movies pages without reloading the application.

13. Fetch API was used to connect the React frontend with FastAPI backend APIs for login, registration, movie search, and favorites.

14. FastAPI was used to create REST APIs with routes for authentication, movie searching, and favorite movie operations.

15. SQLAlchemy ORM was used to interact with the SQLite database and manage users and favorite movie records.

16. JWT authentication was implemented using access tokens to secure protected routes like favorites APIs.

17. Passlib bcrypt hashing was used to securely hash user passwords before storing them in the database.

18. OMDb API integration was implemented in the backend service layer to fetch real-time movie data.

19. Conditional rendering was used in React to display loading messages, errors, and API responses dynamically.

20. Separate CSS files were used to style components and create a clean, responsive user interface.
